---
// Shipping & returns (§6): honest, split by fulfillment path (POD vs packed-by-artist).
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Shipping & returns · GoteFigure" description="How GoteFigure orders ship: printed-to-order apparel and locally printed posters and stickers.">
  <section class="info">
    <h1>Shipping &amp; returns</h1>

    <h2>Two kinds of packages</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Tees &amp; hoods</strong> are printed to order. Nothing sits in a warehouse.
      They usually print in 2-5 business days, then ship. <strong>Posters and stickers</strong>
      are printed locally in California and packed by the artist, typically out the door in 2-4 days.
    </p>
    <p>
      Order both? They’ll arrive as <em>separate packages</em>, possibly days apart.
      That’s not a mistake. It’s two different print shops doing their thing.
    </p>

    <h2>Returns</h2>
    <p>
      Wrong size or a misprint on apparel: tell us within 30 days and we’ll make it right.
      Posters and stickers: if it arrives damaged, send a photo and a replacement ships free.
      Changed your mind on a poster? Within 14 days, unopened, we’ll sort a return.
    </p>

    <h2>Where we ship</h2>
    <p>United States at launch. Elsewhere, just <a href="/info/contact/" class="squiggle">ask</a>; the rabbit is flexible.</p>

    <p class="margin-note">questions? a human (the only human here) answers every email</p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .info { max-width: 680px; margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--s-12) var(--s-6) var(--s-24); }
  .info h1 { margin-bottom: var(--s-6); }
  .info h2 { margin: var(--s-8) 0 var(--s-2); font-size: var(--text-lg); }
  .info p { margin-bottom: var(--s-3); }
</style>
